<br>
Put all of them on shorter timers, like 3 minutes. When I think &quot;berserker,&quot; I imagine someone who goes berserk more often than once every 7 minutes. The duration for the effects should be equalized and at shorter durations than current ones, something like 15 seconds. The shorter durations would balance out being able to use the powers more often. I would really prefer an ability that's usable more often but doesn't last as long.<br>
<br>
Next, the specific changes to the class abilities:<br>
<br>
Berserkers should have a hp boost while their ability is active, like the hero's ability, but not as powerful since berserkers will have a damage advantage. The added hp represent the berserker's ability to keep on fighting after taking a whole bunch of hits and somewhat counteracts their lack of parry. At the same time, they have an endurance boost. They keep the same damage boost.<br>
<br>
Blademasters should have the ability to activate any positional or reactive style at will while their triple wield is up, even when the opening requirements for initiating the style are not met. The positional and reactive styles normally represent taking advantage of openings in the enemy defense to do superior attacks. By distracting the foe, the third blade helps to create openings where they normally would not exist, allowing the blademaster to continously use better styles for a while. The third blade also has a chance to redirect the effects of hostile spells that hit the blademaster, like a Jedi's lightsaber redirects blaster shots. The spell effect is redirected at the blademaster's current target, or at the original caster if the blademaster has targetted nobody. The target of redirection must be within range of the spell's caster, or the caster just gets hit. The subject must simply be targetted, not necessarily attacked. The ability works even if the blademaster is just part of an enemy AoE. He redirects the portion of the effect he would have suffered. If the blademaster is standing within an allied AoE, there is a check to make his target take the effects that the blademaster would have suffered had he not been allied with the caster. If the target redirected at would have been hit by the AoE anyway, he acts as if only hit by one spell effect, but only counts as a character half his true level and having half his resistances for purposes of calculating power of the spell. The redirection chance should be based on the blademaster's parry. Of course, the triple wield is also a damage add, as usual, but should be toned down a little because the redirection ability is pretty strong.<br>
<br>
Mercenary dirty tricks should actually have a chance to blind the enemy with a successful attack while the ability is active. By blindness, I don't mean the fumble chance. Eliminate the fumble entirely, and instead make the enemy player's screen black for a few seconds when he's hit to actually BLIND him. At the same time, the target looses the ability to stick, face, or follow, so he really is blind. He can keep attacking or cast spells or whatever, but he doesn't know whether or not the merc is in front of him, so he'll have a lot of trouble actually hitting a merc with anything. The merc, of course, doesn't stay in the target's forward arc to get hit, but moves around to the side to do positionals and stuff. This ability would be much more useful against casters than the current dirty tricks. They aren't bothered by a little fumble chance. They could freak out and run, but wouldn't know what they are running into. Assassins who target a blinded foe can use backstab or perforate artery without being in stealth mode (since the target can't see them anyway). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 393<br> <font color=#000000>(5/30/03 2:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> -</span><hr size=1> I think that would be a bit too good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap w