<br>
As I said before, blindness in RvR is turning the enemy player's screen black and negating his face/stick/follow.<br>
<br>
In PvE, the monster would be &quot;blinded&quot; by still keeping its initial target selected (whoever it was attacking before being blinded) but then continually spinning around in circles as it attacks (trying to find the target in every direction). If it happens to be facing in the right direction (at its original target) during its attack, then the attack is resolved normally. If it is not facing the original target, then the attack does nothing, even if it is facing somebody else. It cannot select a new target while blind, but aggro can build up as normal, and once it can see again, it can select a new target based on its level of aggro then. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tatsumaruiii>TatsumaruIII</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theotaku.com/trigun/pictures/trigun12/Simage_12.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#000000>(6/3/03 5:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theotaku.com/trigun/pictures/trigun12/Simage_12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;blindness&quot; DT in PvE</span><hr size=1> &quot;I take it your studying the Britons versus Saxon era (when arthur probably lived) rather than the &quot;legendary&quot; arthurian knights era (which could never have been <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )?&quot;<br>
